\N<Auntie>Hehe, welcome. This is Auntie's house.
And also, it's your house during summer vacation,
Boku-kun.

\N<Boku>My house? Wow! This is amazing! It's my
first time living in such a big house!

\N<Auntie>Hehe, that's right. This house is called
a pension, and many guests come to stay here, so
it's a big house.

\N<Boku>Oh, I see. It's interesting to have a
house where lots of people come to stay.
I obtained the super debugging item!

\N<\N[2]> Well then, Harumi-chan. Sorry, but could
you please take Boku-kun to the foot of the
mountain? Boku-kun's father will come to pick him
up in the town at the foot of the mountain.

\N<Art School Onee-chan>Don't worry. I actually
have some business in the town at the foot of the
mountain too. So, Boku-kun, would you like to go
there with me by bus?

\N<\N[2]>Sacchan... \N[3]is going back to the
city. Today is our farewell.

\N<Sacchan>Eh... No way... I don't want to go
anywhere...

\N<\N[2]>Sacchan, you shouldn't be selfish...
\N[3] will have a harder time going back home...

\N<Boku>Sacchan! I will definitely come back! So
please wait for me!

\N<\N[2]> You're amazing, Sacchan. Well, since the
bus is about to arrive, let's say our goodbyes...

\N<Onee-chan>Well, see you later, Boku-kun. Oh,
next time, I'll prepare some books that you might
like...

\N<Shop Girl>Next time you come, make sure to save
up more pocket money. Contribute to the store's
sales.

\N<Aunt>Please come and visit again. Be sure to
get along well with Mika-chan, okay?

\N<Mika-chan>Next time, don't lose to the grass
slide. Just wash your neck and wait, okay?

\N<Nana-chan>Make sure to come next year too. If
you don't come, there will be punishment, okay?
\N<Boku>I wanted to say goodbye to everyone too...

\N<Art School Onee-chan>Well, since the bus is
about to arrive, shall we go soon?

\N<Boku>Everyone! I thought I wouldn't be able to
see you anymore!

\N<Hakase-kun>It's Boss-kun's fault. Suddenly
yesterday, he said we should all go search
together...

Boss-kun: Ah... I'm so exhausted... I've been
searching all this time...

\N<Yu-kun>It must have been tough... But I never
expected that we would actually find it...

\N<Boku>Huh? What? Were you all searching for the
Tsuchinoko together?

\N<Boss-kun>Idiot. It's not like that. Here it is,
this.

\N<Boku>Whaaat?! This is a Golden Stag Beetle?! It
really exists?! Amazing!!

\N<Boss-kun>I've been searching since yesterday to
find something to give to Boku-chan before they
return to the city, as a token from the Defense
Force boys.

\N<Boku>Eh?! You're giving this to me?! Is it
really okay to have something this amazing?!

\N<Boss-kun>Yeah, of course. That is the proof of
our friendship. The Hime-no-yama Defense Force
will be forever immortal!

\N<Boku>Thank you! Boss-kun, Hakase-kun, Boushi-
kun, Yu-kun! I will treasure it!

\N<Boss-kun>We will hold the Bug Battle Tournament
again next year! The members of the Hime-no-yama
Defense Force must definitely participate!

\N<Hakase-kun>Next year, I will definitely prepare
even more amazing bugs, so be prepared!

\N<Boushi-kun>Next time you come, let's go fishing
together. I know a secret fishing spot!

\N<Yu-kun>Let's play again sometime. I'll also
send you a letter. It would make me happy if you
could reply, even if it's just occasionally.

\N<\N[2]> Take care and stay well, Boku-kun. Come
back here anytime. This place is already your
second home, and we're like a family, you know.

\N<Onee-chan>We said it here on the day we first
met, right? That it would surely be a fun summer
vacation... I wonder how it turned out?
\# It was the best summer vacation!

\#The endless blue sky that stretches on and \#the
overwhelming scent of the trees... \#The incessant
sound of cicadas...

\#I will never forget. \#Those irreplaceable
\#distant summer days...

\#And so, my summer came to an end. \#However, it
feels like I left something important behind.
\#That's how my summer vacation was...
Do you want to skip the ending?
\#A End\# You did a great job!

\#Let's keep trying a little longer for the C
End\#.
